ANNEX

TO THE AGREEMENT BETWEEN THE GOVERNMENT OF THE FRENCH

REPUBLIC AND THE ORGANISATION OF EASTERN CARIBBEAN STATES

(OECS) CONCERNING THE ACCESSION OF THE REGION OF GUADELOUPE

AS AN ASSOCIATE MEMBER

This Annex lists the areas of cooperation identified by the Parties (the Region of Guadeloupe and the (rganisation of Eastern Caribbean States) in the context of the accession of Guadeloupe as an Associate Member.

This identification is based notably on existing cooperation projects and particularly on projects such as CARES in the health field and CARIBSKY in that of air connections.

As a member of the ORCS, Guadeloupe will make increased efforts to foster synergies benveen the FU EDIand ERDI instruments forjoint projects involving current ORCS members.

The use of instruments such as Interreg Caribbcan is necessary to cooperate in the following fields:

a.

Transport;

b. Biodirersin, the environment and climate change issues;

c. Disaster preparedness and management;

d. Health and medical scrvices;

c. Tourism and yachting;

f. Education, culture, sport and linguistic diversity;

g. Development of alterative energy sources;

h. Trade information exchange and facilitation.

